<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-21T19:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-21T19:41:00-05:00" n="617" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d617">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/22178</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tampico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tampico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-21T18:00:00-06:41">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Banditti last night attacked terminals of Eureka Coast Oil Co., American,
                            and Corona Co., Dutch Shell, three miles from Tampico. Attacked wife of
                            British employee of Dutch company, and were finally beaten off by armed
                            employees of Eureka Coast Co. Several Mexicans killed or wounded.
                            Embassy advised.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>